#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:2
msgid "同源策略"
msgstr "Same-Origin Policy"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:5
msgid "简介"
msgstr "Introduction"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:6
msgid ""
"同源策略限制了不同源之间如何进行资源交互，是用于隔离潜在恶意文件的重要安全机制。 "
"是否同源由URL决定，URL由协议、域名、端口和路径组成，如果两个URL的协议、域名和端口相同，则表示他们同源。"
msgstr ""
"The same-origin policy restricts how resources interact across different "
"origins and is an important security mechanism for isolating potentially "
"malicious files. Whether two resources are same-origin is determined by the "
"URL. A URL consists of a scheme, domain, port, and path. If two URLs have the "
"same scheme, domain, and port, they are considered same-origin."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:10
msgid "file域的同源策略"
msgstr "Same-Origin Policy for file Origins"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:11
msgid "在之前的浏览器中，任意两个file域的URI被认为是同源的。本地磁盘上的任何HTML文件都可以读取本地磁盘上的任何其他文件。"
msgstr ""
"In earlier browsers, any two file URI origins were considered same-origin. "
"Any HTML file on the local disk could read any other file on the local disk."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:13
msgid "从Gecko 1.9开始，文件使用了更细致的同源策略，只有当源文件的父目录是目标文件的祖先目录时，文件才能读取另一个文件。"
msgstr ""
"Starting with Gecko 1.9, files use a more granular same-origin policy. A file "
"can read another file only when the parent directory of the source file is an "
"ancestor directory of the target file."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:16
msgid "cookie的同源策略"
msgstr "Same-Origin Policy for Cookies"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:17
msgid "cookie使用不同的源定义方式，一个页面可以为本域和任何父域设置cookie，只要是父域不是公共后缀(public suffix)即可。"
msgstr ""
"Cookies use a different origin definition. A page can set cookies for its own "
"domain and for any parent domain, as long as the parent domain is not a "
"public suffix."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:19
msgid ""
"不管使用哪个协议(HTTP/HTTPS)或端口号，浏览器都允许给定的域以及其任何子域名访问cookie。设置 cookie时，可以使用 "
"``domain`` / ``path`` / ``secure`` 和 ``http-only`` 标记来限定其访问性。"
msgstr ""
"Regardless of the protocol (HTTP/HTTPS) or port, browsers allow the given "
"domain and any of its subdomains to access cookies. When setting cookies, the "
"``domain``, ``path``, ``secure``, and ``http-only`` attributes can be used to "
"limit their accessibility."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:21
msgid "所以 ``https://localhost:8080/`` 和 ``http://localhost:8081/`` 的Cookie是共享的。"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, cookies are shared between ``https://localhost:8080/`` and "
"``http://localhost:8081/``."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:24
msgid "Flash/SilverLight跨域"
msgstr "Flash/SilverLight Cross-Domain Access"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:25
msgid "浏览器的各种插件也存在跨域需求。通常是通过在服务器配置crossdomain.xml，设置本服务允许哪些域名的跨域访问。"
msgstr ""
"Various browser plugins also need cross-domain access. This is usually done "
"by configuring crossdomain.xml on the server to specify which domains are "
"allowed to access the service cross-domain."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:27
msgid "客户端会请求此文件，如果发现自己的域名在访问列表里，就发起真正的请求，否则不发送请求。"
msgstr ""
"The client requests this file. If it finds its own domain in the allow list, "
"it sends the real request; otherwise it does not send the request."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:30
msgid "源的更改"
msgstr "Changing the Origin"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:31
msgid ""
"同源策略认为域和子域属于不同的域，例如 ``child1.a.com`` 与 ``a.com`` / ``child1.a.com`` 与 "
"``child2.a.com`` / ``xxx.child1.a.com`` 与 ``child1.a.com`` 两两不同源。"
msgstr ""
"The same-origin policy treats domains and subdomains as different domains. "
"For example, ``child1.a.com`` and ``a.com``, ``child1.a.com`` and "
"``child2.a.com``, and ``xxx.child1.a.com`` and ``child1.a.com`` are all "
"cross-origin pairs."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:33
msgid "对于这种情况，可以在两个方面各自设置 ``document.domain='a.com'`` 来改变其源来实现以上任意两个页面之间的通信。"
msgstr ""
"In this case, both sides can set ``document.domain='a.com'`` to change their "
"origin and allow communication between any of the pages above."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:35
msgid "另外因为浏览器单独保存端口号，这种赋值会导致端口号被重写为 ``null`` 。"
msgstr ""
"In addition, because browsers store the port separately, this assignment "
"causes the port to be rewritten as ``null``."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:38
msgid "跨源访问"
msgstr "Cross-Origin Access"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:39
msgid "同源策略控制了不同源之间的交互，这些交互通常分为三类："
msgstr ""
"The same-origin policy controls interactions between different origins. These "
"interactions are usually divided into three categories:"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:41
msgid "通常允许跨域写操作(Cross-origin writes)"
msgstr "Cross-origin writes are usually allowed"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:42
msgid "链接(links)"
msgstr "Links"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:43
msgid "重定向"
msgstr "Redirects"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:44
msgid "表单提交"
msgstr "Form submissions"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:45
msgid "通常允许跨域资源嵌入(Cross-origin embedding)"
msgstr "Cross-origin embedding is usually allowed"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:46
msgid "通常不允许跨域读操作(Cross-origin reads)"
msgstr "Cross-origin reads are usually not allowed"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:48
msgid "可能嵌入跨源的资源的一些示例有："
msgstr "Examples of resources that may be embedded cross-origin include:"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:50
msgid "``<script src=\"...\"></script>`` 标签嵌入跨域脚本。语法错误信息只能在同源脚本中捕捉到。"
msgstr ""
"The ``<script src=\"...\"></script>`` tag embeds cross-origin scripts. Syntax "
"error details can only be captured for same-origin scripts."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:51
msgid ""
"``<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"...\">`` 标签嵌入CSS。由于CSS的松散的语法规则"
"，CSS的跨域需要一个设置正确的Content-Type 消息头。"
msgstr ""
"The ``<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"...\">`` tag embeds CSS. Because CSS has "
"loose syntax rules, cross-origin CSS requires a correctly set Content-Type "
"header."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:52
msgid "``<img>`` / ``<video>`` / ``<audio>`` 嵌入多媒体资源。"
msgstr "``<img>`` / ``<video>`` / ``<audio>`` embed multimedia resources."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:53
msgid "``<object>`` ``<embed>`` 和 ``<applet>`` 的插件。"
msgstr "Plugins loaded through ``<object>``, ``<embed>``, and ``<applet>``."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:54
msgid ""
"``@font-face`` 引入的字体。一些浏览器允许跨域字体( cross-origin fonts)，一些需要同源字体(same-"
"origin fonts)。"
msgstr ""
"Fonts introduced by ``@font-face``. Some browsers allow cross-origin fonts, "
"while others require same-origin fonts."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:55
msgid "``<frame>`` 和 ``<iframe>`` 载入的任何资源。站点可以使用X-Frame-Options消息头来阻止这种形式的跨域交互。"
msgstr ""
"Any resource loaded by ``<frame>`` and ``<iframe>``. Sites can use the "
"X-Frame-Options header to prevent this form of cross-origin interaction."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:58
msgid "JSONP跨域"
msgstr "JSONP Cross-Domain Access"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:59
msgid ""
"JSONP就是利用 ``<script>`` "
"标签的跨域能力实现跨域数据的访问，请求动态生成的JavaScript脚本同时带一个callback函数名作为参数。"
msgstr ""
"JSONP uses the cross-origin capability of the ``<script>`` tag to access "
"cross-origin data. It requests a dynamically generated JavaScript script and "
"passes a callback function name as a parameter."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:61
msgid "服务端收到请求后，动态生成脚本产生数据，并在代码中以产生的数据为参数调用callback函数。"
msgstr ""
"After the server receives the request, it dynamically generates a script that "
"produces data and calls the callback function with that generated data as an "
"argument."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:63
msgid "JSONP也存在一些安全问题，例如当对传入/传回参数没有做校验就直接执行返回的时候，会造成XSS问题。没有做Referer或Token校验就给出数据的时候，可能会造成数据泄露。"
msgstr ""
"JSONP also has security issues. For example, if incoming or returned "
"parameters are executed directly without validation, XSS can occur. If data "
"is returned without Referer or Token validation, data leakage may occur."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:65
msgid "另外JSONP在没有设置callback函数的白名单情况下，可以合法的做一些设计之外的函数调用，引入问题。这种攻击也被称为SOME攻击。"
msgstr ""
"In addition, when JSONP does not whitelist callback functions, it may "
"legitimately invoke functions outside the intended design and introduce "
"problems. This attack is also called a SOME attack."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:68
msgid "跨源脚本API访问"
msgstr "Cross-Origin Script API Access"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:69
msgid ""
"Javascript的APIs中，如 ``iframe.contentWindow`` , ``window.parent``, "
"``window.open`` 和 ``window.opener`` 允许文档间相互引用。当两个文档的源不同时，这些引用方式将对 "
"``window`` 和 ``location`` 对象的访问添加限制。"
msgstr ""
"In JavaScript APIs, references such as ``iframe.contentWindow``, "
"``window.parent``, ``window.open``, and ``window.opener`` allow documents to "
"reference each other. When two documents have different origins, these "
"reference mechanisms add restrictions on access to the ``window`` and "
"``location`` objects."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:71
msgid "``window`` 允许跨源访问的方法有"
msgstr "Methods of ``window`` that allow cross-origin access include"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:73
msgid "window.blur"
msgstr "window.blur"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:74
msgid "window.close"
msgstr "window.close"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:75
msgid "window.focus"
msgstr "window.focus"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:76
msgid "window.postMessage"
msgstr "window.postMessage"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:78
msgid "``window`` 允许跨源访问的属性有"
msgstr "Properties of ``window`` that allow cross-origin access include"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:80
msgid "window.closed"
msgstr "window.closed"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:81
msgid "window.frames"
msgstr "window.frames"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:82
msgid "window.length"
msgstr "window.length"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:83
msgid "window.location"
msgstr "window.location"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:84
msgid "window.opener"
msgstr "window.opener"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:85
msgid "window.parent"
msgstr "window.parent"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:86
msgid "window.self"
msgstr "window.self"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:87
msgid "window.top"
msgstr "window.top"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:88
msgid "window.window"
msgstr "window.window"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:90
msgid "其中 ``window.location`` 允许读/写，其他的属性只允许读"
msgstr ""
"Among them, ``window.location`` allows reads and writes, while the other "
"properties are read-only"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:93
msgid "跨源数据存储访问"
msgstr "Cross-Origin Data Storage Access"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:94
msgid ""
"存储在浏览器中的数据，如 ``localStorage`` 和 "
"``IndexedDB``，以源进行分割。每个源都拥有自己单独的存储空间，一个源中的Javascript脚本不能对属于其它源的数据进行读写操作。"
msgstr ""
"Data stored in the browser, such as ``localStorage`` and ``IndexedDB``, is "
"partitioned by origin. Each origin has its own separate storage space, and "
"JavaScript from one origin cannot read or write data belonging to another "
"origin."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:97
msgid "CORS"
msgstr "CORS"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:98
msgid ""
"CORS是一个W3C标准，全称是跨域资源共享(Cross-origin resource "
"sharing)。通过这个标准，可以允许浏览器读取跨域的资源。"
msgstr ""
"CORS is a W3C standard whose full name is Cross-Origin Resource Sharing. This "
"standard can allow browsers to read cross-origin resources."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:101
msgid "常见请求头"
msgstr "Common Request Headers"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:102
msgid "Origin"
msgstr "Origin"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:103
msgid "预检请求或实际请求的源站URI, 浏览器请求默认会发送该字段"
msgstr ""
"The source URI of the preflight request or actual request; browsers send this "
"field by default"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:104
msgid "``Origin: <origin>``"
msgstr "``Origin: <origin>``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:105
msgid "Access-Control-Request-Method"
msgstr "Access-Control-Request-Method"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:106
msgid "声明请求使用的方法"
msgstr "Declares the method used by the request"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:107
msgid "``Access-Control-Request-Method: <method>``"
msgstr "``Access-Control-Request-Method: <method>``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:108
msgid "Access-Control-Request-Headers"
msgstr "Access-Control-Request-Headers"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:109
msgid "声明请求使用的header字段"
msgstr "Declares the header fields used by the request"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:110
msgid "``Access-Control-Request-Headers: <field-name>[, <field-name>]*``"
msgstr "``Access-Control-Request-Headers: <field-name>[, <field-name>]*``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:113
msgid "常见返回头"
msgstr "Common Response Headers"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:114
msgid "Access-Control-Allow-Origin"
msgstr "Access-Control-Allow-Origin"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:115
msgid "声明允许访问的源外域URI"
msgstr "Declares the external origin URI that is allowed to access the resource"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:116
msgid "对于携带身份凭证的请求不可使用通配符 ``*``"
msgstr "The wildcard ``*`` cannot be used for requests carrying credentials"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:117
msgid "``Access-Control-Allow-Origin: <origin> | *``"
msgstr "``Access-Control-Allow-Origin: <origin> | *``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:118
msgid "Access-Control-Expose-Headers"
msgstr "Access-Control-Expose-Headers"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:119
msgid "声明允许暴露的头"
msgstr "Declares headers that may be exposed"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:120
msgid ""
"e.g. ``Access-Control-Expose-Headers: X-My-Custom-Header, X-Another-"
"Custom-Header``"
msgstr ""
"e.g. ``Access-Control-Expose-Headers: X-My-Custom-Header, X-Another-"
"Custom-Header``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:121
msgid "Access-Control-Max-Age"
msgstr "Access-Control-Max-Age"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:122
msgid "声明Cache时间"
msgstr "Declares the cache duration"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:123
msgid "``Access-Control-Max-Age: <delta-seconds>``"
msgstr "``Access-Control-Max-Age: <delta-seconds>``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:124
msgid "Access-Control-Allow-Credentials"
msgstr "Access-Control-Allow-Credentials"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:125
msgid "声明是否允许在请求中带入"
msgstr "Declares whether credentials are allowed in the request"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:126
msgid "``Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true``"
msgstr "``Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:127
msgid "Access-Control-Allow-Methods"
msgstr "Access-Control-Allow-Methods"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:128
msgid "声明允许的访问方式"
msgstr "Declares the allowed access methods"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:129
msgid "``Access-Control-Allow-Methods: <method>[, <method>]*``"
msgstr "``Access-Control-Allow-Methods: <method>[, <method>]*``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:130
msgid "Access-Control-Allow-Headers"
msgstr "Access-Control-Allow-Headers"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:131
msgid "声明允许的头"
msgstr "Declares the allowed headers"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:132
msgid "``Access-Control-Allow-Headers: <field-name>[, <field-name>]*``"
msgstr "``Access-Control-Allow-Headers: <field-name>[, <field-name>]*``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:135
msgid "防御建议"
msgstr "Defense Recommendations"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:136
msgid "如非必要不开启CORS"
msgstr "Do not enable CORS unless necessary"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:137
msgid "定义详细的白名单，不使用通配符，仅配置所需要的头"
msgstr ""
"Define a detailed allowlist, do not use wildcards, and configure only the "
"required headers"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:138
msgid "配置 ``Vary: Origin`` 头部"
msgstr "Configure the ``Vary: Origin`` header"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:139
msgid "如非必要不使用 ``Access-Control-Allow-Credentials``"
msgstr "Do not use ``Access-Control-Allow-Credentials`` unless necessary"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:140
msgid "限制缓存的时间"
msgstr "Limit the cache duration"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:143
msgid "阻止跨源访问"
msgstr "Blocking Cross-Origin Access"

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:144
msgid ""
"阻止跨域写操作，可以检测请求中的 ``CSRF token`` ，这个标记被称为Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)"
" 标记。"
msgstr ""
"To block cross-origin writes, detect the ``CSRF token`` in the request. This "
"token is called a Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) token."

#: ../../source/vuln/xss/sop.rst:146
msgid ""
"阻止资源的跨站读取，因为嵌入资源通常会暴露信息，需要保证资源是不可嵌入的。但是多数情况下浏览器都不会遵守 ``Content-Type`` "
"消息头。例如如果在HTML文档中指定 ``<script>`` 标记，则浏览器会尝试将HTML解析为JavaScript。"
msgstr ""
"To block cross-site reads of resources, ensure that resources cannot be "
"embedded, because embedded resources often expose information. In many cases, "
"however, browsers do not strictly honor the ``Content-Type`` header. For "
"example, if a ``<script>`` tag is specified in an HTML document, the browser "
"will try to parse the HTML as JavaScript."
